cs.DM, cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.NA, cs.CC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is a likely category as the paper deals with determining or estimating the diameter of Cayley networks, which is a topic in discrete mathematics. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a likely category as the paper presents an algorithm for obtaining an estimate of the diameter of Cayley graphs generated by transposition trees. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is a possible category as the paper deals with graphs and trees, which are topics in computational geometry. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is a possible category as the paper presents an algorithm for obtaining an estimate of the diameter, which involves numerical computations. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as the paper discusses the time complexity of the previously known estimate for the diameter and presents an algorithm with improved time complexity.
